{
  "texts": [
    "To adapt RoBERTa for the intent classification task, a finetuning approach will be employed.",
    "Specifically, we will append a task-specific classification layer on top of the RoBERTa model and utilize a suitable loss function to optimize for intent classification and sentiment analysis.Fine-tuning of the RoBERTa model involves optimizing its pre-trained weights for the specific task of intent classification.",
    "The addition of a classification layer facilitates the model's adaptation to the nuances of intent expressions.",
    "This process is governed by a task-specific dataset, and the learning objective is defined by a suitable loss function designed to minimize classification errors.",
    "Specifically, the intent classification and sentiment analysis results are predicted using c = argmax(Y) where c is the predicted class, and Y is the probability vector of Y = sof tmax(W h+b)."
  ]
}